t and VoxTell transformer decoder prefix initialization. Runtime memory and position tensors now use the VoxTell-compatible <code>b c d h w -&gt; b h w d c -&gt; (h w d) b c</code> flatten order, and the generated position tensor matches memory token count, batch size, dtype, device, and channel count.</p>\n    <p>Added <code>--init-transformer-from-voxtell</code> to load only <code>transformer_decoder.*</code> tensors from <code>fold_0/checkpoint_final.pth</code> / <code>network_weights</code>. The loader strips the prefix, validates exact key and shape equality against <code>model.transformer_decoder.state_dict()</code>, and calls <code>model.transformer_decoder.load_state_dict(..., strict=True)</code>. No encoder, decoder, projector, or <code>pos_embed</code> path is loaded.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Files Changed</h2>\n    <table>\n      <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py</code></td><td>HWD runtime position contract, prefix-only loader, strict compatibility metadata.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/train.py</code></td><td>Added <code>--init-transformer-from-voxtell</code>; loads before optimizer construction; logs and stores metadata in checkpoint config.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/scripts/audit_voxtell_alignment.py</code></td><td>Added CPU <code>transformer_decoder.</code> prefix audit and HTML reporting.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py</code></td><td>Added non-cubic HWD flatten/position contract test and prefix-loader filtering test.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P5-P6-lite/audit_voxtell_alignment.html</code></td><td>Generated CPU alignment audit report.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P5-P6-lite/RESULT.html</code></td><td>This result report.</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n    <p class=\"meta\">Pre-existing modified files observed and left untouched: <code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/workflow_manifest.yaml</code>, <code>workflow_status.html</code>, and <code>workflow_status.json</code>.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Verification</h2>\n    <h3>Model shape tests</h3>\n    <pre>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py\n\ncollected 10 items\nBody-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py .......... [100%]\n10 passed in 16.92s</pre>\n\n    <h3>CPU prefix audit</h3>\n    <pre>conda run -n voxtell python Body-Tell/scripts/audit_voxtell_alignment.py \\\n  --config Body-Tell/configs/phase1_voxtell_aligned.yaml \\\n  --html-output Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P5-P6-lite/audit_voxtell_alignment.html\n\nTransformer decoder prefix audit\n  status: PASS\n  prefix: transformer_decoder.\n  loaded tensors: 110\n  loaded params: 251,858,944\n  missing: 0\n  unexpected: 0\n  shape mismatches: 0</pre>\n\n    <h3>GPU availability and smoke</h3>\n    <pre>conda run -n voxtell python -c \"import torch; print(torch.cuda.is_available()); ...\"\n\nTrue\nNVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090</pre>\n    <pre>conda run -n voxtell python -c \"[aligned model, load VoxTell prefix, forward/loss/backward on CUDA]\"\n\ngpu_smoke=pass loss=0.667088 logits_shape=(1, 1, 64, 64, 64) loaded_tensors=110 loaded_params=251858944</pre>\n    <p class=\"meta\">A first 32^3 smoke attempt was invalid because the aligned six-stage residual encoder reduces the final stage to 1x1x1, which <code>InstanceNorm3d</code> rejects in training mode. The rerun used 64^3 and passed.</p>\n\n    <h3>Transformer parity</h3>\n    <pre>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_voxtell_transformer_compat.py\n\ncollected 1 item\nBody-Tell/tests/test_voxtell_transformer_compat.py . [100%]\n1 passed in 13.75s</pre>\n\n    <h3>Whitespace</h3>\n    <pre>git diff --check -- Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py Body-Tell/train.py Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py Body-Tell/scripts/audit_voxtell_alignment.py\n\npassed with no output</pre>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Acceptance Checklist</h2>\n    <table>\n      <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Criterion</th><th>Evidence</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>P5 is not an independent <code>pos_embed</code> implementation stage.</td><td>Only runtime deterministic position generation was adjusted.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>No <code>fixed_voxtell_192</code> and no <code>pos_embed</code> state-dict loading path.</td><td>Loader hard-restricts to <code>transformer_decoder.</code>; <code>pos_embed</code> is listed as excluded metadata only.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Runtime position encoding uses selected feature H,W,D and matches memory tokens, batch, dtype, device, and channels.</td><td><code>test_runtime_memory_and_pos_use_voxtell_hwd_flatten_contract</code>.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Non-cubic input verifies <code>b c d h w -&gt; b h w d c -&gt; (h w d) b c</code>.</td><td>New non-cubic test captures projected bottleneck and transformer memory.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Loader reads <code>fold_0/checkpoint_final.pth</code> <code>network_weights</code> and filters only <code>transformer_decoder.*</code>.</td><td>Loader implementation and prefix-loader unit test.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Filtered keys map exactly to <code>model.transformer_decoder.state_dict()</code>.</td><td>CPU audit: 110 tensors, 251,858,944 params, 0 missing/unexpected/mismatched.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Loading uses <code>model.transformer_decoder.load_state_dict(..., strict=True)</code>.</td><td>Implemented in <code>load_voxtell_transformer_decoder_prefix</code>; exercised in unit and GPU smoke.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Does not load <code>encoder.*</code>, <code>decoder.*</code>, projectors, or <code>pos_embed</code>; no full-model whitelist.</td><td>Prefix-only filter; unit test confirms <code>project_text_embed</code> remains unchanged despite matching non-prefix checkpoint key.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>Logs and saved checkpoint config record init metadata.</td><td><code>train.py</code> logs checkpoint path, prefix, tensor count, param count and stores metadata in <code>cfg[\"init_transformer_from_voxtell\"]</code> before checkpoint saves.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>CPU prefix audit passes.</td><td><code>audit_voxtell_alignment.py</code> reported PASS.</td></tr>\n        <tr><td class=\"ok\">Pass</td><td>GPU forward/loss/backward smoke passes if GPU is available.</td><td>CUDA available on RTX 4090; 64^3 aligned-model smoke passed.</td></tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Blockers And Risks</h2>\n    <p>No blockers.</p>\n    <p>Residual risk: the CLI checkpoint-save metadata path is implemented but was not exercised by a full training run to disk, because the required verification was prefix audit plus forward/loss/backward smoke. The saved checkpoint code uses the same mutated <code>cfg</code> object for <code>best.pt</code>, smoke checkpoints, and <code>last.pt</code>.</p>\n  </section>\n</main>\n</body>\n</html>\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
